<module name="PWM">
	The PWM peripheral for the AFTx04 allows the user to create and manipulate signals to their discretion. The PWM includes the functionality to modify the period and duty cycle of the output. The user can create upto 10 different PWN signals routed to predefined GPIO pins. Functionality for left and center aligned modes is provided at both high and low polarity.

	<register name="PWME" offset="0x00">
		This is a 9-bit register. Each bit corresponds to a different PWM pin. Setting a bit will set the corresponding pin.

		<field name = "PWME0">
